@startuml
actor Client
participant "Assessment Controller" as Controller
participant "Assessment Service" as Service
participant "Energy Adapter" as Energy
participant "Weather Adapter" as Weather
participant "Carbon Adapter" as Carbon

Client -> Controller: POST /submitEnergyAssessment\n{requestId:"REQ-1001", createdAt:"2026-03-15T10:00:00Z",\nproperty:{propertyId:"PROP-001", location:"Leicester green cold", propertyType:"home"},\ntimeWindow:{startDateTime:"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z", endDateTime:"2026-03-02T00:00:00Z", granularity:"hourly"}}
Controller -> Service: submitAssessment(request)
Service -> Energy: getEnergyAnalysis(request)
Energy --> Service: totalKWh=13.92, peakKWh=2.5, sourceName=MockSmartMeterAdapter
Service -> Weather: getWeatherContext(request)
Weather --> Service: summary="Cold weather increased heating demand..."
Service -> Carbon: getCarbonIntensityContext(request, totalKWh)
Carbon --> Service: region="Leicester green cold", estimatedKgCO2=1.67
Service --> Controller: 201 Created\nassessmentStatus=Completed
Controller --> Client: SubmitEnergyAssessmentResponse

== Failure branch ==
Client -> Controller: POST /submitEnergyAssessment\npropertyId="FAIL-ENERGY-001"
Controller -> Service: submitAssessment(request)
Service -> Energy: getEnergyAnalysis(request)
Energy --> Service: throws critical energy unavailable
Service --> Controller: 201 Created\nassessmentStatus=Failed, errorMessage=...
Controller --> Client: SubmitEnergyAssessmentResponse
@enduml
